grady@netcom.com (1016/2EF221) writes:
> The control is in the user's hands.  Where it belongs.  The right to 
> develop and record one's innermost thoughts in absolute privacy 
> transcends the authority of any government. 

If you want *absolute* privacy, don't write them down or type them into a 
computer.  It's not things that you don't want anyone to know that you 
encrypt--it's things you only want specific people to know.


